-- AMC Networks Shares Post Their Biggest Drop in Three Months
-- B y   A l e x   S h e r m a n
-- 2012-08-14T20:30:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-14/amc-networks-shares-post-their-biggest-decline-in-three-months.html
AMC Networks Inc., the company
behind “Mad Men” and “The Walking Dead” on  cable television ,
fell 4.5 percent, the biggest decline in three months.  AMC shares dropped to $41.16 at the close in New York. The
stock had climbed 15 percent this year through yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
